A Papilio memnon is a species of butterfly found in Southeast Asia, especially in Indonesia.
It has wings that are mainly black and white in color with elongated tails on the hindwings.
The forewings have yellow spots and a few red spots near the base.
The hindwings have a blue patch with red spots near the base and a single yellow spot above it.
The underside of the wings is brownish-grey with a series of black and white stripes.
Papilio memnon is commonly found in tropical rainforests, but can also be seen in gardens and parks.
It is recognized for its elongated tails on the hindwings that mimic antennae, a common feature in the Papilio genus.
